    RegistryHolder<API,ENTRY>
    During the registry loading phase, some values can be references to values to-be-loaded in the future, or inlined, anonymous values that already exist.

    A holder that contains an inlined registry entry, an anonymous value (does not have a key).

    A holder that references a registry value by key, but does not have the entry itself.
